The evidence with the title 'Most immigrants arrested by ICE have prior criminal convictions ' says Feb 15, 2018  ... Immigrants with past criminal convictions accounted for 74 % of all arrests  ... Criminal convictions accounted for the majority ( 61 % ) of those arrested by the agency.  ... ICE also only reports criminal charge categories with at least 1,000 total  ... In half of the ice areas , non-criminal arrests rose 200% or more. 
